revision.text:
In [[mathematics]], the '''Auslander algebra''' of an algebra ''A'' is the [[endomorphism ring]] of the sum of the [[indecomposable module]]s of ''A''. It was introduced by {{harvs|txt|authorlink=Maurice Auslander|last=Auslander|year=1974}}.

An [[Artin algebra]] Γ is called an '''Auslander algebra''' if gl dim Γ ≤ 2 and if 0→Γ→''I''→''J''→''K''→0 is a minimal [[injective resolution]] of Γ then ''I'' and ''J'' are projective  Γ-modules;

