An '''orthonormal function system (ONS)''' is an [[orthonormal]] [[basis (linear algebra)|basis]] in a [[vector space]] of [[Function (mathematics)|functions]].<ref>{{citation|title=Companion to Concrete Mathematics|series=Dover Books on Mathematics|first=Z. A.|last=Melzak|publisher=Courier Dover Corporation|year=2012|isbn=9780486135816|page=138|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aZ-_GxnhsUgC&pg=RA1-PA138}}.</ref>

See [[basis (linear algebra)]], [[Fourier analysis]], [[square-integrable]], [[Hilbert space]] for more.

